definition: to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]
to pay/to hand over to/classifier for pairs or sets of things

sentences.english: It delivers value more slowly to everyone. Invariably.
sentences.chinese: 这会让交付价值变得更慢，对所有客户都会变慢。

sentences.english: Implementing customer scenarios to include the flow of defect submissions expands integration coverage.
sentences.chinese: 包含缺陷交付流程的实施客户场景扩展了集成的范围。

sentences.english: Weekly con calls will be setup to monitor progress along with documentation of deliverables.
sentences.chinese: 除了交付的文件，每周还要举行电话会谈以监督进程。

sentences.english: I am sure it delivers high-quality products.
sentences.chinese: 我很确定他交付了高质量的产品。

sentences.english: How can the results of data mining be delivered to analysts and employees who need it?
sentences.chinese: 如何将数据挖掘的结果交付给需要它的分析师和雇员？

sentences.english: Airbus delivered 18 of its A380 superjumbo last year.
sentences.chinese: 空中客车交付18架其A380超巨型飞机去年。

sentences.english: This leaves time in each task for the manual delivery of the paper.
sentences.chinese: 这为每个任务留下了手工交付书面文档的时间。

sentences.english: Only deliverables and activities belong on the WBS.
sentences.chinese: 只有可交付成果和活动属于WBS。

sentences.english: Article 212 The pledge right shall be established after the pledgee has delivered the pledged properties.
sentences.chinese: 第二百一十二条质权自出质人交付质押财产时设立。

sentences.english: The donee must take delivery and accept the transfer of ownership.
sentences.chinese: 受赠人应受领交付并接收所有权的转移。

sentences.english: The clavichord was on the auction block.
sentences.chinese: 这架古钢琴被交付拍卖。

sentences.english: Different interpretations of the same term increase the risk of failed project delivery.
sentences.chinese: 对同一术语有不同的解释会增加项目交付失败的风险。

sentences.english: "I'm gonna pay my bills, " Perry says, "especially the oil bills! "
sentences.chinese: 我要去交付我的账单了，佩里说道，尤其是油钱。

sentences.english: The form of decision for administrative penalty shall be given to the party on the spot.
sentences.chinese: 行政处罚决定书应当当场交付当事人。

sentences.english: In other words, these features will be part of the deliverable system.
sentences.chinese: 换句话说，这些特性将是交付系统的一部分。

sentences.english: Dseas get to offer a toll to pass the bridge.
sentences.chinese: 司机过桥必需得交付过桥费。

definition: to procure (for an enterprise etc)/to purchase
to serve in the army/in active service
to finish work/to complete a project
to pay in full/to pay all of a bill/to pay off
to put sth on the market
to order goods/to place an order
to put into production/to put into operation
